WEBVTT

00:00.422 --> 00:01.604
<i>My name is Michael Westen.</i>
<i>I used to be a spy until...</i>

00:04.635 --> 00:07.012
We got a burn notice
on you. You're blacklisted.

00:07.014 --> 00:09.521
<i>When you're burned,</i>
<i>you've got nothing -</i>

00:09.588 --> 00:12.284
<i>no cash, no credit,</i>
<i>no job history.</i>

00:12.352 --> 00:14.651
<i>You're stuck in whatever city</i>
<i>they decide to dump you in.</i>

00:14.715 --> 00:16.615
- Where am I?
- Miami.

00:17.107 --> 00:20.349
<i>You do whatever work</i>
<i>comes your way.</i>

00:20.416 --> 00:22.978
<i>You rely on anyone</i>
<i>who's still talking to you.</i>

00:23.046 --> 00:24.577
<i>A trigger-happy</i>
<i>ex-girlfriend...</i>

00:24.645 --> 00:26.213
Should we shoot them?

00:26.281 --> 00:28.713
<i>...An old friend who used</i>
<i>to inform on you to the FBI...</i>

00:28.780 --> 00:31.182
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.249 --> 00:33.549
<i>...Family, too...</i>
<i>Hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:33.616 --> 00:35.751
<i>...If you're desperate.</i>
<i>Someone needs your help, Michael.</i>

00:35.819 --> 00:38.385
Bottom line --
<i>as long as you're burned,</i>

00:38.453 --> 00:40.054
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

00:42.000 --> 00:48.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:53.381 --> 00:55.515
<i>In any surveillance operation,</i>

00:55.583 --> 00:58.485
<i>you have to resist the impulse</i>
<i>to grab your target</i>

00:58.486 --> 00:59.853
<i>and interrogate him</i>
<i>immediately.</i>

00:59.921 --> 01:01.222
<i>It may be tempting,</i>

01:01.289 --> 01:03.555
<i>particularly</i>
<i>when your target was, say,</i>

01:03.623 --> 01:05.289
<i>involved in framing you</i>
<i>for a murder.</i>

01:09.692 --> 01:12.224
<i>Of course, just because</i>
<i>it's the right way to do things</i>

01:12.292 --> 01:13.825
<i>doesn't make it fun.</i>

01:21.863 --> 01:23.831
We've been here
<i>two</i> days, Sam.

01:23.899 --> 01:26.933
Face it -- this guy is not
calling the shots.

01:27.001 --> 01:29.235
He has Christmas lights
hanging in July.

01:29.303 --> 01:31.037
He may look a little bit
like Michael,

01:31.104 --> 01:33.473
but there is no way he's capable
of killing a CIA officer

01:33.541 --> 01:34.908
and setting Michael up
for it.

01:34.975 --> 01:37.276
Yeah, well, I don't think
he's capable of setting a table.

01:37.344 --> 01:38.511
Yesterday,
I found a brochure

01:38.579 --> 01:40.545
about raising Alpacas for profit
in his trash.

01:40.613 --> 01:42.246
So let's scrap
this cloak and dagger

01:42.314 --> 01:43.581
and go have a little chat.

01:43.648 --> 01:45.449
I'm wearing my door-kicking
Jimmy Choos.

01:45.517 --> 01:46.717
Fi, you know the drill.

01:46.785 --> 01:48.918
You want to find out
who this guys works for,

01:48.985 --> 01:50.185
you hang back and watch.

01:53.555 --> 01:55.855
What if he doesn't live
through the day?

01:55.923 --> 01:58.123
Oh, crap.

01:59.859 --> 02:01.325
A sledgehammer
and some guns.

02:01.393 --> 02:03.126
I don't think they're here
to play bridge.

02:04.695 --> 02:05.762
And you're smiling.

02:05.830 --> 02:06.997
We get to do it my way.

02:07.064 --> 02:08.197
No, we don't,

02:08.264 --> 02:09.899
'cause we can't risk
being exposed.

02:09.967 --> 02:11.134
Well,
we have to do something.

02:11.202 --> 02:12.268
Yes, what we have to do

02:12.336 --> 02:14.270
is orchestra
Jacob's miraculous escape

02:14.337 --> 02:15.538
from the Mac-10 brigade.

02:15.605 --> 02:19.108
All right. Head in.
Let's make it peaceful.

02:19.175 --> 02:20.275
I'll meet you both
out back --

02:20.343 --> 02:21.710
unless a little war
breaks out.

02:21.778 --> 02:23.612
Fi...No war.

02:23.680 --> 02:26.248
Fine. No war.

02:32.588 --> 02:34.856
Mr. Pickles?

02:34.924 --> 02:37.292
Is that you, pal?

02:37.359 --> 02:38.693
Hey, Jacob.

02:38.761 --> 02:40.194
Wait, look,
don't kill me, please!

02:40.262 --> 02:41.829
Ah, don't you worry
about a thing.

02:41.897 --> 02:43.797
I'm not here to kill you.

02:43.865 --> 02:45.566
<i>They're</i> here to kill you.

02:45.633 --> 02:46.900
Wait a second.
Who are you?

02:46.968 --> 02:48.335
Never mind.
I'll explain later.

02:48.403 --> 02:49.703
You need to go out
the back.

02:49.771 --> 02:51.004
There's a tiny, little woman
in a Hyundai

02:51.072 --> 02:52.306
who's gonna protect you.

02:52.373 --> 02:54.274
Ah. Here we go.

02:54.342 --> 02:55.542
Hang on.

02:55.609 --> 02:57.076
Don't forget Mr. Pickles.

02:57.144 --> 02:59.478
A-aren't you coming?

02:59.546 --> 03:01.280
No, I'm gonna cover
your escape.

03:01.348 --> 03:03.716
So I need the keys to the truck
in your garage and this hat.

03:03.783 --> 03:04.750
Yeah, I-I --

03:04.817 --> 03:05.750
No more talking.

03:05.818 --> 03:07.085
Time to go. Now.

03:07.152 --> 03:08.052
Bye, Mr. Pickles.

03:08.120 --> 03:09.520
<i>As a spy,</i>

03:09.588 --> 03:11.021
<i>a lot of missions</i>
<i>depend on the world</i>

03:11.089 --> 03:12.523
<i>not knowing you're there.</i>

03:14.125 --> 03:16.492
<i>When an op involves</i>
<i>saving someone's life</i>

03:16.560 --> 03:18.627
<i>and keeping</i>
<i>your presence unknown,</i>

03:18.695 --> 03:21.096
<i>you have to make their escape</i>
<i>look credible.</i>

03:22.231 --> 03:25.333
<i>So if the person you're saving</i>
<i>is an untrained civilian,</i>

03:25.401 --> 03:28.335
<i>you need to make it look liked</i>

03:28.403 --> 03:30.371
<i>like an untrained civilian.</i>

03:36.211 --> 03:37.912
Hi. I'm Jacob.

03:37.979 --> 03:39.113
This guy broke into --

03:39.180 --> 03:41.314
Honey, what just heard
wasn't fireworks.

03:41.382 --> 03:42.916
Get in the damn car.

03:45.597 --> 03:49.297
<font color=#00FF00>Burn Notice 5x07</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Beseiged</font>
